  <title>Class Creation</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this unit, students will learn how to create their own classes with
      instance variables, constructors, and methods.
    </p>

    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>AP Exam Weighting: 10–18%</p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>Class Periods: ~20-22</p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            Time Estimate: 45 minutes per lesson except 90 minutes for 3.3, 3.5,
            and 3.6. 5-10 class periods for review, practice, FRQs, labs,
            progress checks, and assessments.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            AP Classroom Progress Check Unit 3 Part A: Topics 3.1–3.4,
            Multiple-choice: ~12 questions
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            AP Classroom Progress Check Unit 3 Part B: Topics 3.5–3.9,
            Multiple-choice: ~15 questions, Free-response: 2 questions on Class
            Design
          </p>
        </li>
         <li>
          <p>
            AP Classroom Unit 3 Lab: Virtual Pet Lab Activities 1-4 recommended. 
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </introduction>

